description: REST API and Server Action design standards
glob: ["**/api/**/*.ts", "**/actions/**/*.ts"]
---

## Server Actions (Preferred)

- Define in separate files with "use server" directive
- Validate inputs with Zod before processing
- Return typed results: `{ success: boolean, data?: T, error?: string }`
- Use revalidatePath after mutations

## API Routes (When Needed)

- Use for webhooks, external integrations, and streaming responses
- Validate request body with Zod
- Return proper HTTP status codes:
  - 200: Success
  - 201: Created
  - 400: Bad request / validation error
  - 401: Unauthorized
  - 404: Not found
  - 500: Internal server error
- Always wrap in try/catch with meaningful error messages

## Error Handling

```typescript
// Pattern for Server Actions
try {
  const validated = schema.parse(input)
  const result = await db.insert(table).values(validated)
  revalidatePath("/path")
  return { success: true, data: result }
} catch (error) {
  return { success: false, error: "Failed to create resource" }
}
```

## Security

- Never trust client input — always validate server-side
- Use Clerk's auth() to verify authentication
- Check authorization (user owns the resource) before mutations
